         <head>The louvre exhibition</head>
         
         <p>During the Second French War against Italy, which took place between 1799 and 1801, 
               the French army seized numerous Italian works of art. In 1802, the Louvre Museum organized an art exhibition showcasing the most significant pieces acquired during this campaign. 
               The exhibition quickly gained widespread popularity and provoked a variety of reactions in the contemporary press. Many of these press reviews are now archived at 
               the Bibliothèque nationale de France (BnF).
               
               Our project involves analyzing and encoding three selected reviews : "Journal du Publiciste", "Journal des Débats", and "Journal des Arts" 
               based on their themes and content.
               The goal of this project is to identify the different works of art that were shown at this event. 
               
               To do this, we have created three rules in our ODD:
               
               
               - We have added a list of metadata for <gi>msIdentifier</gi> to give more details about the specific copies of the journal extracts we are using.
            - We have made it mandatory to add a Wikidata ID idno to the name of each artist in <gi>persName</gi>. 
            - We have added an <gi>objectName</gi> element with a type attribute to describe the nature of each artwork more precisely.  </p>
            
